The paper focuses on index set selection for database workloads, which falls under the category of database systems (cs.DB). The paper also discusses the use of deep reinforcement learning (RL) for this task, which is a popular topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of permutation learning, which is a subfield of discrete mathematics and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the challenges of tuning computer system configurations, which is a topic in software engineering (cs.SE).
